message.text:
Hi there, 𝒂𝒔𝒑𝒊𝒓𝒊𝒏𝒈 𝑬𝒙𝒆𝒄𝒖𝒕𝒊𝒗𝒆 𝑪𝒐𝒎𝒎𝒊𝒕𝒕𝒆𝒆 𝒎𝒆𝒎𝒃𝒆𝒓𝒔 𝒐𝒇 𝒕𝒉𝒆 𝑰𝑻𝑯𝑴 𝑺𝒕𝒖𝒅𝒆𝒏𝒕 𝑪𝒐𝒖𝒏𝒄𝒊𝒍! ✨

Still undecided about which office you’d like to join?

We warmly invite you to be part of the 𝗢𝗳𝗳𝗶𝗰𝗲 𝗼𝗳 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗔𝘂𝗱𝗶𝘁𝗼𝗿 (𝗢𝗔𝗨𝗗)!

✨𝐎𝐟𝐟𝐢𝐜𝐞𝐫-𝐢𝐧-𝐜𝐡𝐚𝐫𝐠𝐞:
Mx. Bulaong, Sanjim Jayver

The Office of the Auditor is composed of two departments:

📌𝐀𝐮𝐝𝐢𝐭 𝐃𝐞𝐩𝐚𝐫𝐭𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐭:
𝘿𝙞𝙧𝙚𝙘𝙩𝙤𝙧: Buenaventura, Breanna
𝘼𝙨𝙨𝙤𝙘𝙞𝙖𝙩𝙚 𝘿𝙞𝙧𝙚𝙘𝙩𝙤𝙧𝙨: Sapiera, Gab & Albano, Joaquin

𝑹𝒐𝒍𝒆𝒔 𝒂𝒏𝒅 𝑭𝒖𝒏𝒄𝒕𝒊𝒐𝒏𝒔:
✨Ensure integrity, accountability, and transparency in the Student Council’s financial and operational activities.
✨Assist in crafting and evaluating audited reports on the Council’s expenditures and disbursements.

📌𝐑𝐞𝐬𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐜𝐡 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐃𝐚𝐭𝐚 𝐀𝐧𝐚𝐥𝐲𝐭𝐢𝐜𝐬 𝐃𝐞𝐩𝐚𝐫𝐭𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐭 (𝐑𝐀𝐃𝐀):

𝑹𝒐𝒍𝒆𝒔 𝒂𝒏𝒅 𝑭𝒖𝒏𝒄𝒕𝒊𝒐𝒏𝒔:
✨Collaborate with the Student’s Welfare and Grievances Department to create survey questions, gather data, and evaluate student concerns.
✨Facilitate and provide research-driven information and comprehensive data analysis regarding student concerns.

message.text:
Hi there, 𝒂𝒔𝒑𝒊𝒓𝒊𝒏𝒈 𝑬𝒙𝒆𝒄𝒖𝒕𝒊𝒗𝒆 𝑪𝒐𝒎𝒎𝒊𝒕𝒕𝒆𝒆 𝒎𝒆𝒎𝒃𝒆𝒓𝒔 𝒐𝒇 𝒕𝒉𝒆 𝑰𝑻𝑯𝑴 𝑺𝒕𝒖𝒅𝒆𝒏𝒕 𝑪𝒐𝒖𝒏𝒄𝒊𝒍! ✨

Still undecided about which office you’d like to join?

We warmly invite you to be part of the 𝗢𝗳𝗳𝗶𝗰𝗲 𝗼𝗳 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗔𝘂𝗱𝗶𝘁𝗼𝗿 (𝗢𝗔𝗨𝗗)!

✨𝐎𝐟𝐟𝐢𝐜𝐞𝐫-𝐢𝐧-𝐜𝐡𝐚𝐫𝐠𝐞:
Mx. Bulaong, Sanjim Jayver

The Office of the Auditor is composed of two departments:

📌𝐀𝐮𝐝𝐢𝐭 𝐃𝐞𝐩𝐚𝐫𝐭𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐭:
𝘿𝙞𝙧𝙚𝙘𝙩𝙤𝙧: Buenaventura, Breanna
𝘼𝙨𝙨𝙤𝙘𝙞𝙖𝙩𝙚 𝘿𝙞𝙧𝙚𝙘𝙩𝙤𝙧𝙨: Sapiera, Gab & Albano, Joaquin

𝑹𝒐𝒍𝒆𝒔 𝒂𝒏𝒅 𝑭𝒖𝒏𝒄𝒕𝒊𝒐𝒏𝒔:
✨Ensure integrity, accountability, and transparency in the Student Council’s financial and operational activities.
✨Assist in crafting and evaluating audited reports on the Council’s expenditures and disbursements.

📌𝐑𝐞𝐬𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐜𝐡 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐃𝐚𝐭𝐚 𝐀𝐧𝐚𝐥𝐲𝐭𝐢𝐜𝐬 𝐃𝐞𝐩𝐚𝐫𝐭𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐭 (𝐑𝐀𝐃𝐀):
𝘿𝙞𝙧𝙚𝙘𝙩𝙤𝙧: Alagaban, Armie
𝘼𝙨𝙨𝙤𝙘𝙞𝙖𝙩𝙚 𝘿𝙞𝙧𝙚𝙘𝙩𝙤𝙧𝙨: Alejandro, Kaly & Ilagan, Dexter

𝑹𝒐𝒍𝒆𝒔 𝒂𝒏𝒅 𝑭𝒖𝒏𝒄𝒕𝒊𝒐𝒏𝒔:
✨Collaborate with the Student’s Welfare and Grievances Department to create survey questions, gather data, and evaluate student concerns.
✨Facilitate and provide research-driven information and comprehensive data analysis regarding student concerns.

𝙒𝙚 𝙖𝙧𝙚 𝙩𝙧𝙪𝙡𝙮 𝙚𝙭𝙘𝙞𝙩𝙚𝙙 𝙩𝙤 𝙬𝙚𝙡𝙘𝙤𝙢𝙚 𝙮𝙤𝙪 𝙩𝙤 𝙤𝙪𝙧 𝙊𝘼𝙐𝘿 𝙛𝙖𝙢𝙞𝙡𝙮! 𝙏𝙤𝙜𝙚𝙩𝙝𝙚𝙧, 𝙬𝙚 𝙬𝙞𝙡𝙡 𝙨𝙪𝙥𝙥𝙤𝙧𝙩 𝙤𝙣𝙚 𝙖𝙣𝙤𝙩𝙝𝙚𝙧 𝙖𝙣𝙙 𝙬𝙤𝙧𝙠 𝙝𝙖𝙣𝙙 𝙞𝙣 𝙝𝙖𝙣𝙙 𝙩𝙤 𝙗𝙧𝙞𝙣𝙜 𝙤𝙪𝙩 𝙩𝙝𝙚 𝙗𝙚𝙨𝙩 𝙛𝙤𝙧 𝙩𝙝𝙚 𝙗𝙚𝙩𝙩𝙚𝙧𝙢𝙚𝙣𝙩 𝙤𝙛 𝙩𝙝𝙚 𝙄𝙏𝙃𝙈 𝙨𝙩𝙪𝙙𝙚𝙣𝙩 𝙗𝙤𝙙𝙮!🫶🏻

𝑨𝑷𝑷𝑳𝒀 𝑵𝑶𝑾!: https://forms.office.com/r/BVPMhCkmqF?origin=lprLink

Mx. Bulaong, Sanjim Jayver

The Office of the Auditor is composed of two departments:

📌𝐀𝐮𝐝𝐢𝐭 𝐃𝐞𝐩𝐚𝐫𝐭𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐭:

✨Ensure integrity, accountability, and transparency in the Student Council’s financial and operational activities.
✨Assist in crafting and evaluating audited reports on the Council’s expenditures and disbursements.

Hi there, 𝒂𝒔𝒑𝒊𝒓𝒊𝒏𝒈 𝑬𝒙𝒆𝒄𝒖𝒕𝒊𝒗𝒆 𝑪𝒐𝒎𝒎𝒊𝒕𝒕𝒆𝒆 𝒎𝒆𝒎𝒃𝒆𝒓𝒔 𝒐𝒇 𝒕𝒉𝒆 𝑰𝑻𝑯𝑴 𝑺𝒕𝒖𝒅𝒆𝒏𝒕 𝑪𝒐𝒖𝒏𝒄𝒊𝒍! ✨

Still undecided about which office you’d like to join?

We warmly invite you to be part of the 𝗢𝗳𝗳𝗶𝗰𝗲 𝗼𝗳 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗔𝘂𝗱𝗶𝘁𝗼𝗿 (𝗢𝗔𝗨𝗗)!

✨𝐎𝐟𝐟𝐢𝐜𝐞𝐫-𝐢𝐧-𝐜𝐡𝐚𝐫𝐠𝐞:
Mx. Bulaong, Sanjim Jayver

The Office of the Auditor is composed of two departments:

📌𝐀𝐮𝐝𝐢𝐭 𝐃𝐞𝐩𝐚𝐫𝐭𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐭:
𝘿𝙞𝙧𝙚𝙘𝙩𝙤𝙧: Buenaventura, Breanna
𝘼𝙨𝙨𝙤𝙘𝙞𝙖𝙩𝙚 𝘿𝙞𝙧𝙚𝙘𝙩𝙤𝙧𝙨: Sapiera, Gab & Albano, Joaquin

𝑹𝒐𝒍𝒆𝒔 𝒂𝒏𝒅 𝑭𝒖𝒏𝒄𝒕𝒊𝒐𝒏𝒔:
✨Ensure integrity, accountability, and transparency in the Student Council’s financial and operational activities.
✨Assist in crafting and evaluating audited reports on the Council’s expenditures and disbursements.

📌𝐑𝐞𝐬𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐜𝐡 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐃𝐚𝐭𝐚 𝐀𝐧𝐚𝐥𝐲𝐭𝐢𝐜𝐬 𝐃𝐞𝐩𝐚𝐫𝐭𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐭 (𝐑𝐀𝐃𝐀):
𝘿𝙞𝙧𝙚𝙘𝙩𝙤𝙧: Alagaban, Armie
𝘼𝙨𝙨𝙤𝙘𝙞𝙖𝙩𝙚 𝘿𝙞𝙧𝙚𝙘𝙩𝙤𝙧𝙨: Alejandro, Kaly & Ilagan, Dexter

𝑹𝒐𝒍𝒆𝒔 𝒂𝒏𝒅 𝑭𝒖𝒏𝒄𝒕𝒊𝒐𝒏𝒔:
✨Collaborate with the Student’s Welfare and Grievances Department to create survey questions, gather data, and evaluate student concerns.
✨Facilitate and provide research-driven information and comprehensive data analysis regarding student concerns.

𝙒𝙚 𝙖𝙧𝙚 𝙩𝙧𝙪𝙡𝙮 𝙚𝙭𝙘𝙞𝙩𝙚𝙙 𝙩𝙤 𝙬𝙚𝙡𝙘𝙤𝙢𝙚 𝙮𝙤𝙪 𝙩𝙤 𝙤𝙪𝙧 𝙊𝘼𝙐𝘿 𝙛𝙖𝙢𝙞𝙡𝙮! 𝙏𝙤𝙜𝙚𝙩𝙝𝙚𝙧, 𝙬𝙚 𝙬𝙞𝙡𝙡 𝙨𝙪𝙥𝙥𝙤𝙧𝙩 𝙤𝙣𝙚 𝙖𝙣𝙤𝙩𝙝𝙚𝙧 𝙖𝙣𝙙 𝙬𝙤𝙧𝙠 𝙝𝙖𝙣𝙙 𝙞𝙣 𝙝𝙖𝙣𝙙 𝙩𝙤 𝙗𝙧𝙞𝙣𝙜 𝙤𝙪𝙩 𝙩𝙝𝙚 𝙗𝙚𝙨𝙩 𝙛𝙤𝙧 𝙩𝙝𝙚 𝙗𝙚𝙩𝙩𝙚𝙧𝙢𝙚𝙣𝙩 𝙤𝙛 𝙩𝙝𝙚 𝙄𝙏𝙃𝙈 𝙨𝙩𝙪𝙙𝙚𝙣𝙩 𝙗𝙤𝙙𝙮!🫶🏻

Hi there, 𝒂𝒔𝒑𝒊𝒓𝒊𝒏𝒈 𝑬𝒙𝒆𝒄𝒖𝒕𝒊𝒗𝒆 𝑪𝒐𝒎𝒎𝒊𝒕𝒕𝒆𝒆 𝒎𝒆𝒎𝒃𝒆𝒓𝒔 𝒐𝒇 𝒕𝒉𝒆 𝑰𝑻𝑯𝑴 𝑺𝒕𝒖𝒅𝒆𝒏𝒕 𝑪𝒐𝒖𝒏𝒄𝒊𝒍! ✨

Still undecided about which office you’d like to join?

We warmly invite you to be part of the 𝗢𝗳𝗳𝗶𝗰𝗲 𝗼𝗳 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗔𝘂𝗱𝗶𝘁𝗼𝗿 (𝗢𝗔𝗨𝗗)!

✨𝐎𝐟𝐟𝐢𝐜𝐞𝐫-𝐢𝐧-𝐜𝐡𝐚𝐫𝐠𝐞:
Mx. Bulaong, Sanjim Jayver

The Office of the Auditor is composed of two departments:

📌𝐀𝐮𝐝𝐢𝐭 𝐃𝐞𝐩𝐚𝐫𝐭𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐭:
𝘿𝙞𝙧𝙚𝙘𝙩𝙤𝙧: Buenaventura, Breanna
𝘼𝙨𝙨𝙤𝙘𝙞𝙖𝙩𝙚 𝘿𝙞𝙧𝙚𝙘𝙩𝙤𝙧𝙨: Sapiera, Gab & Albano, Joaquin

✨Ensure integrity, accountability, and transparency in the Student Council’s financial and operational activities.
✨Assist in crafting and evaluating audited reports on the Council’s expenditures and disbursements.

📌𝐑𝐞𝐬𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐜𝐡 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐃𝐚𝐭𝐚 𝐀𝐧𝐚𝐥𝐲𝐭𝐢𝐜𝐬 𝐃𝐞𝐩𝐚𝐫𝐭𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐭 (𝐑𝐀𝐃𝐀):
𝘿𝙞𝙧𝙚𝙘𝙩𝙤𝙧: Alagaban, Armie
𝘼𝙨𝙨𝙤𝙘𝙞𝙖𝙩𝙚 𝘿𝙞𝙧𝙚𝙘𝙩𝙤𝙧𝙨: Alejandro, Kaly & Ilagan, Dexter

𝑹𝒐𝒍𝒆𝒔 𝒂𝒏𝒅 𝑭𝒖𝒏𝒄𝒕𝒊𝒐𝒏𝒔:
✨Collaborate with the Student’s Welfare and Grievances Department to create survey questions, gather data, and evaluate student concerns.
✨Facilitate and provide research-driven information and comprehensive data analysis regarding student concerns.

𝙒𝙚 𝙖𝙧𝙚 𝙩𝙧𝙪𝙡𝙮 𝙚𝙭𝙘𝙞𝙩𝙚𝙙 𝙩𝙤 𝙬𝙚𝙡𝙘𝙤𝙢𝙚 𝙮𝙤𝙪 𝙩𝙤 𝙤𝙪𝙧 𝙊𝘼𝙐𝘿 𝙛𝙖𝙢𝙞𝙡𝙮! 𝙏𝙤𝙜𝙚𝙩𝙝𝙚𝙧, 𝙬𝙚 𝙬𝙞𝙡𝙡 𝙨𝙪𝙥𝙥𝙤𝙧𝙩 𝙤𝙣𝙚 𝙖𝙣𝙤𝙩𝙝𝙚𝙧 𝙖𝙣𝙙 𝙬𝙤𝙧𝙠 𝙝𝙖𝙣𝙙 𝙞𝙣 𝙝𝙖𝙣𝙙 𝙩𝙤 𝙗𝙧𝙞𝙣𝙜 𝙤𝙪𝙩 𝙩𝙝𝙚 𝙗𝙚𝙨𝙩 𝙛𝙤𝙧 𝙩𝙝𝙚 𝙗𝙚𝙩𝙩𝙚𝙧𝙢𝙚𝙣𝙩 𝙤𝙛 𝙩𝙝𝙚 𝙄𝙏𝙃𝙈 𝙨𝙩𝙪𝙙𝙚𝙣𝙩 𝙗𝙤𝙙𝙮!🫶🏻

message.text:
[Groovers ’25-’26: Tatak Tamaraw 2025–ITHM Plenary & Program Orientation - Intermission Performance]

🎖 Boots hit the ground. Heads held high. Precision in every step.

We proudly present the performance of the FEU ITHM Groovers of “𝐀𝐅𝐓𝐄𝐑 𝐆𝐑𝐎𝐔𝐍𝐃”, staged during the 𝗧𝗮𝘁𝗮𝗸 𝗧𝗮𝗺𝗮𝗿𝗮𝘄 𝟮𝟬𝟮𝟱–𝗜𝗧𝗛𝗠 𝗣𝗹𝗲𝗻𝗮𝗿𝘆 & 𝗣𝗿𝗼𝗴𝗿𝗮𝗺 𝗢𝗿𝗶𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻 on 𝗔𝘂𝗴𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝟳, 𝟮𝟬𝟮𝟱.

Thank you to the event organizers and to everyone who showed up, cheered loud, and witnessed the charge firsthand.

We’re not done—𝘵𝘩𝘪𝘴 𝘪𝘴 𝘰𝘯𝘭𝘺 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘣𝘦𝘨𝘪𝘯𝘯𝘪𝘯𝘨.

This is ₳₣₮ɆⱤ ₲ⱤØɄ₦Đ.
We move as one.

⸻

We proudly present the performance of the FEU ITHM Groovers of “𝐀𝐅𝐓𝐄𝐑 𝐆𝐑𝐎𝐔𝐍𝐃”, staged during the 𝗧𝗮𝘁𝗮𝗸 𝗧𝗮𝗺𝗮𝗿𝗮𝘄 𝟮𝟬𝟮𝟱–𝗜𝗧𝗛𝗠 𝗣𝗹𝗲𝗻𝗮𝗿𝘆 & 𝗣𝗿𝗼𝗴𝗿𝗮𝗺 𝗢𝗿𝗶𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻 on 𝗔𝘂𝗴𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝟳, 𝟮𝟬𝟮𝟱.

Thank you to the event organizers and to everyone who showed up, cheered loud, and witnessed the charge firsthand.

We’re not done—𝘵𝘩𝘪𝘴 𝘪𝘴 𝘰𝘯𝘭𝘺 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘣𝘦𝘨𝘪𝘯𝘯𝘪𝘯𝘨.

This is ₳₣₮ɆⱤ ₲ⱤØɄ₦Đ.
We move as one.

[Groovers ’25-’26: Tatak Tamaraw 2025–ITHM Plenary & Program Orientation - Intermission Performance]

🎖 Boots hit the ground. Heads held high. Precision in every step.

We proudly present the performance of the FEU ITHM Groovers of “𝐀𝐅𝐓𝐄𝐑 𝐆𝐑𝐎𝐔𝐍𝐃”, staged during the 𝗧𝗮𝘁𝗮𝗸 𝗧𝗮𝗺𝗮𝗿𝗮𝘄 𝟮𝟬𝟮𝟱–𝗜𝗧𝗛𝗠 𝗣𝗹𝗲𝗻𝗮𝗿𝘆 & 𝗣𝗿𝗼𝗴𝗿𝗮𝗺 𝗢𝗿𝗶𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻 on 𝗔𝘂𝗴𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝟳, 𝟮𝟬𝟮𝟱.

Thank you to the event organizers and to everyone who showed up, cheered loud, and witnessed the charge firsthand.

We’re not done—𝘵𝘩𝘪𝘴 𝘪𝘴 𝘰𝘯𝘭𝘺 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘣𝘦𝘨𝘪𝘯𝘯𝘪𝘯𝘨.

This is ₳₣₮ɆⱤ ₲ⱤØɄ₦Đ.
We move as one.

⸻

🎖 Boots hit the ground. Heads held high. Precision in every step.

We proudly present the performance of the FEU ITHM Groovers of “𝐀𝐅𝐓𝐄𝐑 𝐆𝐑𝐎𝐔𝐍𝐃”, staged during the 𝗧𝗮𝘁𝗮𝗸 𝗧𝗮𝗺𝗮𝗿𝗮𝘄 𝟮𝟬𝟮𝟱–𝗜𝗧𝗛𝗠 𝗣𝗹𝗲𝗻𝗮𝗿𝘆 & 𝗣𝗿𝗼𝗴𝗿𝗮𝗺 𝗢𝗿𝗶𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻 on 𝗔𝘂𝗴𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝟳, 𝟮𝟬𝟮𝟱.

Thank you to the event organizers and to everyone who showed up, cheered loud, and witnessed the charge firsthand.

We move as one.

[Groovers ’25-’26: Tatak Tamaraw 2025–ITHM Plenary & Program Orientation - Intermission Performance]

🎖 Boots hit the ground. Heads held high. Precision in every step.

We proudly present the performance of the FEU ITHM Groovers of “𝐀𝐅𝐓𝐄𝐑 𝐆𝐑𝐎𝐔𝐍𝐃”, staged during the 𝗧𝗮𝘁𝗮𝗸 𝗧𝗮𝗺𝗮𝗿𝗮𝘄 𝟮𝟬𝟮𝟱–𝗜𝗧𝗛𝗠 𝗣𝗹𝗲𝗻𝗮𝗿𝘆 & 𝗣𝗿𝗼𝗴𝗿𝗮𝗺 𝗢𝗿𝗶𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻 on 𝗔𝘂𝗴𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝟳, 𝟮𝟬𝟮𝟱.

Thank you to the event organizers and to everyone who showed up, cheered loud, and witnessed the charge firsthand.

We’re not done—𝘵𝘩𝘪𝘴 𝘪𝘴 𝘰𝘯𝘭𝘺 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘣𝘦𝘨𝘪𝘯𝘯𝘪𝘯𝘨.

This is ₳₣₮ɆⱤ ₲ⱤØɄ₦Đ.
We move as one.

⸻

Lorenz Oraa

message.text:
[Groovers ’25-’26: Tatak Tamaraw 2025–ITHM Plenary & Program Orientation - Intermission Performance]

🎖 Boots hit the ground. Heads held high. Precision in every step.

We proudly present the performance of the FEU ITHM Groovers of “𝐀𝐅𝐓𝐄𝐑 𝐆𝐑𝐎𝐔𝐍𝐃”, staged during the 𝗧𝗮𝘁𝗮𝗸 𝗧𝗮𝗺𝗮𝗿𝗮𝘄 𝟮𝟬𝟮𝟱–𝗜𝗧𝗛𝗠 𝗣𝗹𝗲𝗻𝗮𝗿𝘆 & 𝗣𝗿𝗼𝗴𝗿𝗮𝗺 𝗢𝗿𝗶𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻 on 𝗔𝘂𝗴𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝟳, 𝟮𝟬𝟮𝟱.

Thank you to the event organizers and to everyone who showed up, cheered loud, and witnessed the charge firsthand.

We’re not done—𝘵𝘩𝘪𝘴 𝘪𝘴 𝘰𝘯𝘭𝘺 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘣𝘦𝘨𝘪𝘯𝘯𝘪𝘯𝘨.

This is ₳₣₮ɆⱤ ₲ⱤØɄ₦Đ.
We move as one.

⸻

𝗢𝗩𝗘𝗥𝗔𝗟𝗟 𝗗𝗜𝗥𝗘𝗖𝗧𝗜𝗢𝗡:
Lorenz Oraa

message.text:
[Groovers ’25-’26: Tatak Tamaraw 2025–ITHM Plenary & Program Orientation - Intermission Performance]

🎖 Boots hit the ground. Heads held high. Precision in every step.

We proudly present the performance of the FEU ITHM Groovers of “𝐀𝐅𝐓𝐄𝐑 𝐆𝐑𝐎𝐔𝐍𝐃”, staged during the 𝗧𝗮𝘁𝗮𝗸 𝗧𝗮𝗺𝗮𝗿𝗮𝘄 𝟮𝟬𝟮𝟱–𝗜𝗧𝗛𝗠 𝗣𝗹𝗲𝗻𝗮𝗿𝘆 & 𝗣𝗿𝗼𝗴𝗿𝗮𝗺 𝗢𝗿𝗶𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻 on 𝗔𝘂𝗴𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝟳, 𝟮𝟬𝟮𝟱.

Thank you to the event organizers and to everyone who showed up, cheered loud, and witnessed the charge firsthand.

We’re not done—𝘵𝘩𝘪𝘴 𝘪𝘴 𝘰𝘯𝘭𝘺 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘣𝘦𝘨𝘪𝘯𝘯𝘪𝘯𝘨.

This is ₳₣₮ɆⱤ ₲ⱤØɄ₦Đ.
We move as one.

⸻

𝗢𝗩𝗘𝗥𝗔𝗟𝗟 𝗗𝗜𝗥𝗘𝗖𝗧𝗜𝗢𝗡:
Lorenz Oraa

𝗖𝗛𝗢𝗥𝗘𝗢𝗚𝗥𝗔𝗣𝗛𝗘𝗥𝗦:
Lorenz Oraa
Arthur Bricks Marquez
Lorenzo James Dela Cruz
Paul Muyot Jr.
Jessika Leigh Lagula

Clara Maria Amaranta Torres
Lorenz Oraa

𝗠𝗶𝘅𝗲𝗱 𝗯𝘆:

“Goin Down” by Ace Hood
